text: Jacques Lamblin (born August 29, 1952 in Nancy) is a member of the National Assembly of France. He represents the Meurthe-et-Moselle department, and is a member of the Union for a Popular Movement. ==References== Category:1952 births Category:Living people Category:People from Nancy, France Category:Rally for the Republic politicians Category:Union for a Popular Movement politicians Category:Gaullism, a way forward for France Category:Deputies of the 13th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic Category:Deputies of the 14th National Assembly of the French Fifth Republic
